{
  "text": "Interestingly, given the same physical findings, gender did not play a role within the referral pattern for vascular access. Despite women being underrepresented within the AVF group, the pattern is likely explained by the tendency for women to have smaller vascular diameters and higher primary failure rates, though gender is not an independent predictor of primary failure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
